what is dependency injection in java?
A. In software engineering, dependency injection is a technique whereby one object supplies the dependencies of another object.

What is static binding and dynamic binding?
A. The binding which can be resolved at compile time by compiler is known as static or early binding. Binding of all the static,
private and final methods is done at compile-time .In Dynamic binding compiler doesn’t decide the method to be called.
Overriding is a perfect example of dynamic binding.








